# 🎓 AI-Based Classroom Monitoring System

## 📌 Project Description

The AI-Based Classroom Monitoring System is a smart application that uses computer vision and artificial intelligence to monitor student behavior in a classroom. The system analyzes live video from a webcam and determines whether students are attentive or not. Based on this, it calculates an engagement score and displays it on a web dashboard.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* To monitor student attention in real-time
* To detect faces using computer vision
* To classify students as attentive or inattentive
* To calculate engagement score
* To display results on a web interface

---

## ⚙️ Technologies Used

* Python
* OpenCV
* NumPy
* Flask
* HTML
* CSS

---

## 🧠 Working

1. The system captures live video using a webcam.
2. Each frame is processed using OpenCV.
3. Faces are detected using Haar Cascade Classifier.
4. The system checks face position to determine attention.
5. Engagement score is calculated.
6. The result is displayed on screen and web dashboard.

---

## 📊 Features

* Real-time face detection
* Attention tracking
* Engagement score calculation
* Web dashboard display
* Simple and user-friendly interface

